I move to amend Senate Bill No. 2165 as follows:
1. On Page 3, Line 8, by deleting after the word “as” and before the word “evidence” the word
“primary” and inserting the words “prima facie”;
2. On Page 4, Line 2, by deleting after the word “court” and before the word “order” the word
“may” and inserting the word “shall”;
3. On Page 4, Line 23, by inserting after the number “2.” and before the word “The” the words
“Regardless of whether a pre-birth support order has been issued,”; and
4. On Page 5, Line 3, by inserting after the word “danger” and before the word “may” the words “to
the preborn child”.
